    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "Note, there has been two huge transaction spikes in the last week, one lasting about a day, the other one was a few hours yesterday. It would probably take its toll on weaker machines. Also if you have a ton of connections, then the transactions are potentially propagated by many nodes to you, so you need to verify and dedup much much more of them. Any particular reason for maintaining such a high connection pool?\n",
