    "body": "Could you detail the hardware of those devices? I.e. CPU, RAM, disk type? The issue @drupalnomad was mentioning was caused by the network pingponging invalid transactions, which increased linearly with the number of peers you had (hence why he was hit hard with 200+ connections). In your case if you're using a private network, I don't the same issue holds. Could you open a new thread about it with all the details (so that this one which was fixed can be closed)?\n",
